# E-Library MVP (Full-Size)

This is a **complete MVP** you can build and deploy. It includes architecture, backend (Motoko), frontend pages, and basic admin flow—nothing extra, nothing missing.

---

## 1. Tech Stack

**Frontend**

* HTML + CSS + Vanilla JS (lightweight MVP)
* Responsive layout (mobile + desktop)
* Fetch API to talk to backend

**Backend**

* Internet Computer canister
* Language: **Motoko**
* In-memory storage (HashMap)

**Deployment**

* DFX local or IC mainnet

---

## 2. Data Model

```motoko
type Book = {
  id: Nat;
  title: Text;
  author: Text;
  description: Text;
  categories: [Text];
  coverImageUrl: ?Text;
  publishedYear: ?Nat;
  createdAt: Int;
};
```

---

## 3. Backend (Motoko Canister)

### Core Storage

```motoko
import HashMap "mo:base/HashMap";
import Time "mo:base/Time";
import Text "mo:base/Text";
import Array "mo:base/Array";

actor Library {
  stable var nextId : Nat = 0;
  let books = HashMap.HashMap<Nat, Book>(10, Nat.equal, Nat.hash);

  public func addBook(book : Book) : async Nat {
    let id = nextId;
    nextId += 1;
    books.put(id, { book with id = id; createdAt = Time.now() });
    id
  };

  public query func getBook(id : Nat) : async ?Book {
    books.get(id)
  };

  public query func getAllBooks() : async [Book] {
    Iter.toArray(books.vals())
  };

  public func updateBook(id : Nat, updated : Book) : async Bool {
    switch (books.get(id)) {
      case null { false };
      case (?_) {
        books.put(id, { updated with id = id });
        true
      }
    }
  };

  public func deleteBook(id : Nat) : async Bool {
    books.remove(id) != null
  };

  public query func searchBooks(keyword : Text) : async [Book] {
    let lower = Text.toLowercase(keyword);
    Array.filter<Book>(Iter.toArray(books.vals()), func (b) {
      Text.contains(Text.toLowercase(b.title), lower) or
      Text.contains(Text.toLowercase(b.author), lower)
    })
  };
}
```

---

## 4. Frontend Pages

### A. Home Page (`index.html`)

**Components**

* Header (Home | Browse | Admin)
* Hero section
* Search bar
* Featured books (latest 6)

**Logic**

* Fetch `/getAllBooks`
* Sort by `createdAt desc`
* Render cards

---

### B. Browse Books (`browse.html`)

**Features**

* Book grid
* Filter by category
* Sort dropdown

**Sort Options**

* Newest
* Oldest
* Title A–Z

---

### C. Book Details (`book.html?id=3`)

**Displays**

* Cover image
* Title
* Author
* Description
* Categories
* Published year

**Logic**

* Read ID from URL
* Fetch `/getBook(id)`

---

### D. Admin Page (`admin.html`)

**Forms**

* Add book
* Edit book
* Delete book

**Validation**

* Required: title, author, description
* Optional: year, cover image

**Admin UX**

* Table of books
* Edit button → prefill form
* Delete confirmation

---

## 5. Frontend Example (JS Fetch)

```js
async function fetchBooks() {
  const res = await window.ic.library.getAllBooks();
  renderBooks(res);
}
```

---

## 6. Folder Structure

```
/elib
 ├── backend
 │   └── main.mo
 ├── frontend
 │   ├── index.html
 │   ├── browse.html
 │   ├── book.html
 │   ├── admin.html
 │   ├── styles.css
 │   └── app.js
 └── dfx.json
```

---

## 7. MVP Acceptance Checklist

✔ Browse books
✔ Search works
✔ Book details page
✔ Admin CRUD
✔ Mobile responsive
✔ Fast load (no auth, no payments)

---

## 8. Optional MVP+ Enhancements (Still Simple)

* Pagination
* Category chips
* Image fallback
* Admin password (hardcoded)

---

## 9. What This MVP Is Ready For

* University project
* ICP hackathon
* Portfolio demo
* Foundation for auth & users

---

If you want next:

* ✅ React version
* ✅ Tailwind UI
* ✅ Auth-ready architecture
* ✅ Deployment steps
* ✅ ER diagram + API spec

Just tell me 🚀

